How centralized and formalized is ABC, if at all? ABC Corporation is highly standardized and centralized. The degree of formalization is the extent to which an organization's processes and procedures are standardized and written down. There is a lot of paperwork at ABC Corp., but everyone knows exactly what they're supposed to be doing in their position. There is a well-defined set of policies and procedures that workers must adhere to, indicating a high degree of formalization within the organization. The term "centralization" is used to describe how much power is held by a small group of people at the very top of an organization. Employees lower on the totem pole at ABC Corp. have little say in corporate matters and report to the CEO through a small group of middle management. This is a strong indicator of centralization, since it shows that authority to make decisions rests mostly with a small number of people at the very top of the corporation. 